12/04/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- Parliamentarians from several Southeast European (SEE) states joined their counterparts from Austria and Italy Tuesday (11 April) for a two-day conference on improving co-operation in the fight against organised crime. The event was co-organised by the OSCE, the Albanian legislature, the Stability Pact for SEE and the Austrian Development Agency. It is part of a wider programme aimed at launching a network among parliamentary committees in the region.
Also Tuesday, German Army chief General Wolfgang Schneiderhan visited Tirana. During a meeting with President Alfred Moisiu, he reaffirmed German support for Albania's NATO aspirations. (Albanian News - 12/04/06; UPI, Albanian President Web site - 11/04/06)
